{
  "texts": [
    "Beyond these changes, and minors white space differences, the dataset, and prompts were kept design same as the study in [19].",
    "In [19] the highest achieving model was GPT-4 [25] with a 𝑝𝑎𝑠𝑠@1 pass rate of 43.5% and 60.0% for VerilogEval-human and VerilogEval-machine, respectively.",
    "GPT-3.5 exhibited lower pass rates of 26.7% and 46.7%.We evaluate fourteen publicly available large-language models against these VerilogEval-human code completion prompts:• OpenAI GPT-4o [27] • OpenAI GPT-4 Turbo (gpt-4-1106-preview) [26] • OpenAI GPT-4 (gpt-4-0613) [25] • Mistral AI Mistral Large [1] • Meta Llama3.1 405B, 70B, and 8B [23] • Meta Llama3 70B [23] • Meta Llama2 70B [23] • Meta CodeLlama 70B [22] • Google CodeGemma 7B [13] • DeepSeek Coder 33B and 6.7B [14] • RTL-Coder DeepSeek v1.1 6.7B [20] The models are comprised of a range of closed and open source, parameter sizes, and general-purpose to specialized.",
    "CodeGemma 7B CodeLlama 70B Mistral Large GPT-4 GPT-4 Turbo DeepSeek Coder 33B DeepSeek Coder 6.7B RTL-Coder 6.7B Llama3.1 8B Llama3.1 70B Llama3.1 405B Llama2 70B Llama3 70B GPT-4o 0% 10% 20% 30% 40% 50% 60% 70% 12/5/22 3/15/23 6/23/23 10/1/23 1/9/24 4/18/24 7/27/24 11/4/24 Benchmark Pass Rate (pass@1) Model Release Date Code Completion Pass Rate (n=20, temperature=0.8, top_p=0.95) GPT-4 was the best pass rate when VerilogEval v1 was released.",
    "Llama3.1 achieves the highest pass rate in this work for code completion without addiitonal prompt tuning."
  ]
}